==English==

===Pronunciation===
Pronounced like: arg (the h is silent)

===Interjection===
'''argh!'''
# {{internet}} {{slang}}: An utterance used to express dismay, embarassment or frustration.

===Usage note===
''Arrggh!'', ''Aaaarrrggghhh!!!'' or any repeating series of a, r, g, h, and !, in sequence, conveys the same meaning; all are considered incorrect and/or illiterate nonsense.

